From Geoff Miller Subject Re Ban All Firearms writes Firearms tend to fall into this low dollar pound It would not be economic to smuggle them All production would have to be There are not all that many people who have both the skill AND motivation to assemble worthwhile firearms from High ranking crime figures could obtain imported Uzis and such but the average person and average thug would be lucky to get a zip gun and would pay through the nose for So why did the Australian Customs Service make a public statement to a parliamentary committee last year that weapons smuggling was a problem which it was not able to control Possibly criminals don't have your grasp of economics Geoff Miller Computer Centre Australian Defence Force Academy